dc_description_s: [This feature class contains the location of certified farmland preservation districts as identified in farmland preservation ordinances with both texts and maps that have been certified (or recertified) by DATCP Land and Water Resource Managment (LWRM) Bureau since July 1, 2009. This feature class was created by DATCP by standardizing and aggregating data submitted by counties as part of the farmland preservation plan certification process. This feature class was last updated February 2019. ]
dc_creator_sm: Wisconsin Department of Agriculture, Trade, and Consumer Protection
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For more information please visit: https://datcp.wi.gov/Pages/Programs_Services/GISData.aspx [Zoning jurisdictions that have not been recertified since 2009 are not portrayed. The zoning layer does not account for rezoned parcels.]
